Full Job Description
Overview:
At Page, we’re actively seeking talented people to join an empowered employee environment. Our teams provide architecture, engineering, interiors and consulting services on large, complex projects around the world. As our market sectors and services grow, we continuously add new opportunities. Will you join us?
Responsibilities:
We are searching for a Senior Project Manager to work in our Industrial Market Sector. This position will be located in our Northwest Austin office. The ideal candidate will have experience in a variety of market sectors such as: Semiconductor and Science & Technology. You will lead large design teams for technically sophisticated projects such as; advanced manufacturing for semiconductor, automotive manufacturing centers and battery/energy manufacturing facilities. The Senior Project Manager role involves both client-facing and team-facing responsibilities and has tremendous growth potential.

In addition the responsibilities include:
Forecast and organize project teams for design, development, production and project document delivery;
Coordinate with consultants, team members and the client;
Successfully execute projects by following Page’s and Owner’s protocols and procedures in order to reach the best solution;
Develop strong client, consultant and collaborator relationships;
Understand budget, code and jurisdictional requirements;
Provide monthly project status report including staffing and cashflow projections;
Provide mentorship and guidance to project team;
Collaborate on project fee development and proposals.
Qualifications:
A Degree in engineering, architecture or a related field from an accredited, four-year university;
Professional Engineers or Architecture license preferred;
5+ years of relevant professional experience;
Experience in science and technology, mission critical or similarly complex projects;
Ability to manage multiple project sizes, with a concentration in large projects valued at $30MM plus;
Apply detailing skills and be proficient with construction administrative processes;
Proven effectiveness coordinating with contractors, engineering teams, and consultants;
Proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite, and familiar with BIM, Revit and AutoCAD;
Ability to successfully lead/organize a team of multiple disciplines and consultants;
Confident with public speaking and networking;
Excellent writing skills;
Detail oriented and organized with proven experience in managing multiple projects simultaneously.
